From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter <peter@navq.local>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 09:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mmc: pwrseq_simple: fall back to GPIO when reset control
 unavailable

Since the reset-controller support was added to pwrseq_simple, a power
sequence node that declares exactly one "reset-gpios" line is routed
through devm_reset_control_get_optional_shared() instead of being driven
as a plain GPIO. With CONFIG_RESET_GPIO=y the reset core is expected to
wrap that GPIO into a synthetic "reset-gpio" reset controller.

On the i.MX95 NavQ-B the usdhc3 (SDIO WiFi) power sequence uses a single
reset line that lives on a PCAL6524 I2C GPIO expander:

    usdhc3_pwrseq: usdhc3-pwrseq {
        compatible = "mmc-pwrseq-simple";
        reset-gpios = <&i2c3_ioexp23 16 (GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW | GPIO_OPEN_SOURCE)>;
        post-power-on-delay-ms = <200>;
    };

The reset-controller core cannot wrap this expander line and returns a
hard -EINVAL:

    pwrseq_simple usdhc3-pwrseq: error -EINVAL: reset control not ready
    pwrseq_simple usdhc3-pwrseq: probe ... failed with error -22

Because probe aborts, the mmc-pwrseq provider never appears, the
non-removable SDIO host (mmc@428b0000) stays in deferred probe forever,
the WiFi chip is never powered, and no wlan interface is created.

Don't treat a non-deferred reset-controller error as fatal: honour
-EPROBE_DEFER, but otherwise clear reset_ctrl and fall through to the
existing plain-GPIO reset path, which drives the expander line correctly
(this is how the line was handled before the reset-controller route was
added).

Upstream-Status: Pending [BSP fix; to be submitted to linux-mmc]

Signed-off-by: Peter <peter@navq.local>
---
 drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c | 14 +++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c b/drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c
index 4b47e6c3b04b..98354c7383f7 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c
@@ -137,9 +137,17 @@ static int mmc_pwrseq_simple_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	ngpio = of_count_phandle_with_args(dev->of_node, "reset-gpios", "#gpio-cells");
 	if (ngpio == 1) {
 		pwrseq->reset_ctrl = devm_reset_control_get_optional_shared(dev, NULL);
-		if (IS_ERR(pwrseq->reset_ctrl))
-			return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(pwrseq->reset_ctrl),
-					     "reset control not ready\n");
+		if (IS_ERR(pwrseq->reset_ctrl)) {
+			/*
+			 * A single reset-gpios line that the reset-controller
+			 * core cannot wrap (e.g. an I2C GPIO expander line)
+			 * returns a hard error here. Honour deferral, but
+			 * otherwise fall back to the plain GPIO reset path.
+			 */
+			if (PTR_ERR(pwrseq->reset_ctrl) == -EPROBE_DEFER)
+				return -EPROBE_DEFER;
+			pwrseq->reset_ctrl = NULL;
+		}
 	}
 
 	/*
